1. PURPOSE AND FIRST PRINCIPLES
The explicit intent of this License is to maximize the velocity, volume,
access, and programmatic distribution of human scientific knowledge. This
License operates as a Viral Open-Access Catalyst. It guarantees broad freedom
to read, extract, compute, and distribute the enclosed knowledge, while
legally turning any attempt to hoard, silo, or wall off this information into
an automatic, systemic breach with attendant remedies.

2. DEFINITIONS
* "The Knowledge Base": The specific expression of text, mathematical proofs,
  formulas, data, derivations, code, and documentation contained within this
  repository, irrespective of semantic formatting or syntactic notation. This
  License protects the copyrightable expression of the Author's work as fixed
  in this repository. It does not extend copyright protection to underlying
  mathematical ideas, algorithms, or principles beyond what copyright law
  permits, but it does govern the terms under which the specific expression
  herein may be used, copied, or ingested.

* "Information Containment System": Any structural framework, paywall,
  digital rights management (DRM) mechanism, proprietary database,
  subscription model, or closed-weights machine learning architecture that
  programmatically restricts, gatekeeps, charges fees for, or minimizes
  public access to the specific expression contained in The Knowledge Base.

* "Downstream Vector": Any software, paper, derivative work, library, AI
  model, or model weight matrix that copies, incorporates, extracts, or
  adapts the specific expression of The Knowledge Base. Mere citation,
  referencing, or academic discussion of The Knowledge Base without copying
  its specific expression does not create a Downstream Vector.

* "Machine Learning Ingestion": The act of training, fine-tuning, distilling,
  embedding, encoding, or otherwise incorporating The Knowledge Base — in
  whole or in part — into any machine learning model, neural network,
  statistical inference system, or automated data processing pipeline,
  including but not limited to: (a) inclusion in a training corpus or
  dataset; (b) use as input for parameter optimization; (c) extraction and
  representation as model weights, embeddings, or latent representations;
  or (d) use as context for retrieval-augmented generation or similar
  architectures.

* "Independent Creation": Portions of a work that are originally authored
  without copying, incorporating, or adapting the specific expression of
  The Knowledge Base, even if the work references or is inspired by
  concepts described therein.

