The Author grants a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, perpetual license
to view, use, reproduce, modify, translate, script, and distribute The
Knowledge Base to all humanity. This grant is made expressly subject to the
conditions, obligations, and termination provisions set forth in Sections 4,
5, 5.5, 6, 7, 8, and 9. Any breach of these conditions terminates all rights
granted under this Section automatically and immediately, without further
notice, subject to the cure provisions of Section 7.

  3.A. Limited Permission to Compute: The rights granted above include
  permission to programmatically access and compute upon The Knowledge Base
  for non-commercial scientific research, provided that all conditions of
  Section 4 are satisfied. This grant expressly excludes Machine Learning
  Ingestion as defined in Section 2. Machine Learning Ingestion is governed
  exclusively by Section 5.5 and is not permitted under Section 3.A under
  any interpretation. No provision of this License shall be construed to
  grant, imply, or permit Machine Learning Ingestion except as expressly
  authorized by Section 5.5.A.

4. THE VIRAL PROPAGATION MECHANISM (THE OPEN-ACCESS TRAP)
Your permission to use, distribute, or run computations based on The Knowledge
Base is strictly conditioned upon your adherence to absolute information
transparency:

  A. Mandatory Share-Alike Inheritance: If you build upon, reference, execute,
  or integrate The Knowledge Base into any Downstream Vector, and you
  distribute or deploy that Downstream Vector, the distributed portions of
  that Downstream Vector that copy, incorporate, or derive from The Knowledge
  Base MUST be made publicly available and free under this identical
  License. Portions of a Downstream Vector that constitute Independent
  Creation are not subject to this share-alike obligation and remain the
  intellectual property of their respective authors. Only portions that
  copy, incorporate, or directly adapt the specific copyrightable expression
  of The Knowledge Base must be released under this License.

  B. Anti-Containment Provision: You are strictly prohibited from placing any
  distributed Downstream Vector behind an Information Containment System. For
  purposes of this provision, a Downstream Vector is "distributed" when it is
  made available to any party other than the creator, whether publicly,
  privately, commercially, or through API access.

  C. The Corporate Extraction Remedy: If a commercial enterprise or legacy
  academic institution integrates The Knowledge Base into a proprietary
  matrix, tuition-gated system, or closed-weights model architecture, that
  entity contractually agrees to publicize the portions of its codebase,
  model weights, or dataset that copy, incorporate, or directly derive from
  the copyrightable expression of The Knowledge Base within thirty (30) days
  of deployment. This obligation is strictly limited to materials that copy,
  incorporate, or derive from The Knowledge Base and does not extend to
  unrelated proprietary materials, independently developed code, or trade
  secrets unconnected to The Knowledge Base.

  D. License Compatibility: If The Knowledge Base is combined with software
  or materials licensed under the GNU General Public License version 3.0 or
  later (GPL-3.0+), the GPL-3.0+ terms shall govern the combined work with
  respect to the GPL-licensed components, and this License shall govern
  components derived from The Knowledge Base. Where licenses are
  incompatible and cannot be simultaneously satisfied, the more restrictive
  obligations regarding openness and transparency shall prevail.

5. AUTOMATIC OPENING REMEDY
Any attempt to contain, hide, or commercialize The Knowledge Base in violation
of Sections 4 or 5.5 immediately voids your license to the derivative
materials. Continued deployment within a closed network transforms the
affected system into an unauthorized use, rendering the operator liable for
copyright infringement under applicable law, including but not limited to
17 U.S.C. §§ 501-505 (United States Copyright Act), and equivalent provisions
under the Berne Convention for the Protection of Literary and Artistic Works
as implemented in the operator's jurisdiction. Where the operator's conduct
meets the standard for willful infringement under applicable law, the Author
shall seek enhanced statutory damages to the maximum extent permitted by
law.

5.5. MACHINE LEARNING INGESTION PROHIBITION
Machine Learning Ingestion of The Knowledge Base constitutes creation of a
Downstream Vector and triggers all obligations under Section 4.

  5.5.A. Ingestion Permitted Only With Compliance: No person or entity may
  perform Machine Learning Ingestion of The Knowledge Base unless the
  resulting model, its complete training methodology, and all derived weight
  matrices are made permanently public and free under this identical
  License within thirty (30) days of initial training completion.

  5.5.B. Closed-Weights Ingestion Breach: Training any model on The
  Knowledge Base and subsequently withholding model weights, architecture
  details, or training data constitutes willful copyright infringement under
  applicable law. The Author reserves the right to seek injunctive relief,
  statutory damages, and all other available remedies.

  5.5.C. Technical Infeasibility Fallback: Where technical isolation of
  model weights or training data specifically derived from The Knowledge
  Base is infeasible due to the entangled nature of neural network
  representations, the licensee shall instead pay reasonable compensation to
  the Author equivalent to the fair market value of the infringed material,
  as determined by qualified intellectual property valuation experts. The
  Author retains the right to seek injunctive relief halting the use of any
  model trained on The Knowledge Base regardless of whether compensation is
  paid, offered, or disputed.

  5.5.D. Survival: This Section 5.5 survives any termination of this
  License. Ingestion occurring prior to termination remains subject to all
  obligations herein regardless of subsequent license status.

