7. TERMINATION, CURE, AND NON-WAIVER
  7.A. Automatic Termination: Violation of any provision of this License
  terminates all rights granted herein automatically and immediately upon the
  occurrence of the breach, without prior notice from the Author.

  7.B. Cure Period: A breaching party may reinstate its rights under this
  License by curing the violation within thirty (30) days of discovering or
  being notified of the breach, provided that the cure includes full
  compliance with all affected provisions, including public release of any
  Downstream Vector that was improperly withheld. If the breach involves
  Machine Learning Ingestion in violation of Section 5.5, reinstatement
  additionally requires permanent public disclosure of all affected model
  weights, training data containing The Knowledge Base, and complete
  training methodology, or payment of compensation as provided in Section
  5.5.C where technical infeasibility is demonstrated.

  7.C. No Reinstatement After Litigation: If the Author initiates formal
  legal proceedings for breach of this License prior to the breaching party's
  cure, no reinstatement shall be available, and the breaching party's rights
  under this License are permanently terminated.

  7.D. Reservation of Rights: Nothing in this Section 7 limits the Author's
  right to pursue all available legal and equitable remedies for breaches
  occurring prior to cure, including damages accrued during the period of
  breach.

  7.E. Non-Waiver: No failure or delay by the Author in exercising any
  right, power, or remedy under this License shall operate as a waiver
  thereof, nor shall any single or partial exercise of any right preclude
  any further exercise of that right or any other right. The Author's
  acceptance of any breach, whether known or unknown, shall not constitute
  waiver of any future enforcement rights. This Section 7.E explicitly
  overrides any equitable defense of laches, estoppel, or waiver by conduct
  to the maximum extent permitted by law.

